1
00:00:08,675 --> 00:00:09,801
(Tatsumi) Towa-chan?

2
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:11,302
(Kotaro) Huh?

3
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:14,973
(Rabbitha) Long time no see, Dora

4
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:34,534
(Toshie) Nihao I'm home

5
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:36,494
Ah, a customer?

6
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:38,747
What about Mr. Ryumi?

7
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:42,167
(Torataro) Ah, I just went inside.

8
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,127
-(Rie) Anaguma again? -(Torataro) Yeah.

9
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:50,175
Is Dora a bear? My favorite tactics haven't changed.

10
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:54,262
Ah, uh... Is this a request or something?

11
00:00:54,345 --> 00:00:58,767
Ah, I work as a reporter in the news department of Tokyo Television⸺

12
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,269
My name is Komaki Toba.

13
00:01:04,647 --> 00:01:07,358
I came to ask for representation in court.

14
00:01:09,778 --> 00:01:11,780
♪～

15
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:23,875
～♪

16
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:29,130
Komagi-san for defamation⸺

17
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:30,924
Have you been sued?

18
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:36,554
(Torataro) The person who sued was Ryoma Tsuge, a member of the House of Representatives.

19
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:40,934
(Rie) A young member of the ruling party who was elected three times.

20
00:01:41,017 --> 00:01:44,938
I'm sure he's a former prosecutor who turned to politics, right?

21
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:48,900
About 3 weeks ago I⸺

22
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:52,320
Interview held at the Diet Building

23
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:54,656
(Usaha) Now, let's do an interview right away.

24
00:01:56,574 --> 00:02:01,371
 (Tsuge) Ah, ah... I'm not good at recording⸺

25
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,831
Would you please stop?

26
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:04,207
Ah...

27
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:09,546
I wish I could hear a deeper story without the recording⸺

28
00:02:09,629 --> 00:02:11,381
I'm grateful too

29
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,341
the next day⸺

30
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:17,387
I have uploaded the article I compiled to the station's news site.

31
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:24,727
(Rie) I see, Representative Tsuge will be running for the next presidential election.

32
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,355
The truth behind the rumors that he is running as a candidate⸺

33
00:02:27,438 --> 00:02:29,232
So it was something to confirm.

34
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:32,735
(Usaha) However, right after the article was published, Representative Tsuge came forward⸺

35
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:37,448
I have asked Tokyo TV directly to delete the article and apologize.

36
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:38,366
(Torataro) Huh?

37
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:46,833
According to the complaint, “I have no intention of running for president.”

38
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:50,169
“The article is a fabrication that ignores the person’s wishes⸺”

39
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:53,423
“It seriously damages the reputation of the plaintiff.”

40
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:56,384
Does that completely negate the content of this article?

41
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:58,803
(Usagiha) But I took notes properly⸺

42
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:01,264
Representative Tsuge is positive about the presidential election⸺

43
00:03:01,347 --> 00:03:04,809
It is true that you have said that you are dissatisfied with the party leadership.

44
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:08,438
But did Tokyo TV delete the article?

45
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:14,235
The bureau's executives formally apologized, but I refused.

46
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:18,323
Because of this, Representative Tsuge sued me personally.

47
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:21,326
The plaintiff is Representative Tsuge himself.

48
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:25,205
The defendant, Mr. Komaki, admitted that the contents of the article were unfounded⸺

49
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:28,166
Request for apology in signature article

50
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:29,292
My article is⸺

51
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:31,836
I want to claim that I wasn't wrong.

52
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,338
So to Dora...

53
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:37,717
To Mr. Tatsumi Tendo⸺

54
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,178
I want you to fight this lawsuit.

55
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,890
(Rie) “Dora” is Ms. Ryumi’s⸺

56
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,016
Is it a nickname?

57
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:48,853
Ah... I was the only one who used it.

58
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:54,609
Ryumi's dragon is a dragon, so it's called Dora...

59
00:04:07,872 --> 00:04:10,583
If it's Dora, you'll accept it, right?

60
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:18,925
(Tatsumi) Uh... yeah

61
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:31,854
I'm currently on paid probation.

62
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:35,149
Please call me anytime if you have any court discussions.

63
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:37,276
Excuse me

64
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:40,154
-(Rie) Thank you for your hard work.-(Torataro) Excuse me.

65
00:04:43,366 --> 00:04:46,369
(Sound of door opening and closing)

66
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:49,622
(Rie) Sweets as souvenirs

67
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:51,624
(Tatsuo) Oh, thank you for this.

68
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:54,419
Come to think of it, this was my first time visiting here, right?

69
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:57,297
(Tatsuo) Ah, yes, ah, please go ahead.

70
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:01,509
(Torataro) Actually, I saw Toba Komaki in the office today...

71
00:05:01,592 --> 00:05:02,468
 (Tatsuo) Huh?

72
00:05:08,307 --> 00:05:12,312
Maybe that's why Ryumi-sensei ended up in a cave.

73
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:17,066
(Rie) Um... I can't tell you the details.

74
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:21,821
Mr. Komaki was asked by Dr. Ryumi to represent him in a lawsuit.

75
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:25,700
(Torataro) I am aware that I am trespassing, but⸺

76
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:28,536
Between Tatsumi-sensei and Usaba-san⸺

77
00:05:28,619 --> 00:05:31,622
Could you please tell me what happened?

78
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:36,544
(Tatsuo) Yeah.

79
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:48,431
(Kasumi) Toba-chan is Tatsumi's only friend

80
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:51,309
We were best friends

81
00:05:53,102 --> 00:05:57,398
Among the few girls in an all-male encouragement group

82
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,609
The two quickly became friends⸺

83
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:03,988
We vowed to each other to become professionals.

84
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:10,078
The two of us always spared no time in our sleep to hone each other's shogi skills.

85
00:06:11,329 --> 00:06:15,875
It was worth it 4 years ago when we both did it together⸺

86
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:18,753
I was able to get promoted to 3rd dan.

87
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:23,091
(Tatsumi) Ah, good morning.

88
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:24,759
beautiful

89
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,386
cute

90
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:27,929
(Kashiwade)

91
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:33,226
(Tatsuo) The third-dan league is the gateway to becoming a professional⸺

92
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:39,399
In a league match that lasted half a year, only the two players with the highest scores were promoted to 4th dan.In other words⸺

93
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:42,235
This is how you can become a professional shogi player.

94
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:45,279
There are strict rules there.

95
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:47,115
Even if I get promoted to 3rd dan⸺

96
00:06:47,198 --> 00:06:51,452
I have to win the league match on my 26th birthday⸺

97
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:56,624
At that moment, you will be automatically removed from membership.

98
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:01,879
In that league match, Toba-chan continues to struggle⸺

99
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:06,425
I was on the brink of losing.

100
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:15,059
The last day of the league match is the 1st, with 2 games played⸺

101
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:19,355
A trick of fate, 17 games before the final game⸺

102
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:25,444
Usa-chan and Tatsumi ended up playing against each other.

103
00:07:26,612 --> 00:07:27,280
(sound pointing to pieces)

104
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:29,115
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

105
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:32,285
(sound pointing to pieces)

106
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:33,661
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

107
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:39,125
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

108
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:45,464
The game started with Toba-chan making the first move⸺

109
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:48,885
Tatsumi shows off her offensive piece arrangement just like in the shogi style⸺

110
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:51,596
I have a feeling that Toba-chan will be on the defensive.

111
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:54,640
But in the middle

112
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:57,059
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

113
00:07:57,143 --> 00:08:01,606
Toba-chan takes advantage of Tatsumi's attack and launches a counterattack⸺

114
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:06,485
The final stage was a battle of ups and downs.

115
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:14,452
Ryumi suddenly gained the upper hand from Toba-chan's doubtful moves.

116
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:23,878
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

117
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:34,555
Ordinary Ryumi would keep attacking at once and win within a few moves.

118
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:37,225
That was the situation

119
00:08:42,647 --> 00:08:47,026
But then a long battle began.

120
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:58,037
(Game clock audio) Countdown begins.

121
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,211
40 seconds

122
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:13,135
50 seconds 1 2 3 4⸺

123
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:14,053
5... (sound of pressing the game clock)

124
00:09:14,136 --> 00:09:16,889
(Torataro) Even though Tatsumi-sensei had the upper hand⸺

125
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:18,516
Why a long battle?

126
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:21,394
Tatsumi that day was⸺

127
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:26,440
For some reason, even Toba-chan's energy and fighting spirit are gone⸺

128
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:32,196
I kept pointing my hand as if cutting off my escape and breaking my heart.

129
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:35,658
(Tatsuo) Tatsumi is⸺

130
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,743
I pointed out the hand that would make me lose my friends.

131
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:09,859
(game clock audio) 50 seconds 1 2 3 4 5⸺

132
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:13,195
‪６ ７ ８⸺

133
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,280
9... (sound of pressing the game clock)

134
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:21,412
(Kasumi) And the 100th move of fate

135
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:26,709
If it was Tatsumi's usual attack, she would have been able to attack and defeat him with 6 Nanaku...

136
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:29,629
(game clock audio) 50 seconds 1 2...

137
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:30,755
(Kasumi) What Ryumi was pointing at was...

138
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:36,385
(game clock audio) 4 5 6 7 8 9...

139
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:37,261
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

140
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:40,598
(Kasumi) It's not a big deal or anything⸺

141
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:44,560
A hand that firmly protects one's balls

142
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:08,501
Part 2 is ⸺

143
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:13,047
I gave Toba-chan deep, deep despair.

144
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,425
That's...

145
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:21,013
This way of pointing is said to be rare in the world of shogi⸺

146
00:11:21,097 --> 00:11:23,057
It was the way I lost friends.

147
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:29,897
Ryumi-sensei, why did you do that?

148
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:33,317
We can't even imagine it⸺

149
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,779
I couldn't even ask.

150
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:43,035
If there's an answer, it's only within Ryumi.

151
00:11:44,912 --> 00:11:50,418
And Tatsumi was in the final game on the same day...

152
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:56,382
(Game clock audio) 6 7 8 9 10 Time is up.

153
00:11:58,175 --> 00:12:02,555
(Kasumi) Without making a single move, I ran out of time and lost.

154
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:11,355
And Tatsumi voluntarily withdrew from the encouragement group.

155
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:19,155
Komaki Toba-san had such a past...

156
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:24,243
Why did you go to the trouble of appointing Ryumi-sensei as your agent?

157
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:31,250
(Torataro) Ryumi-sensei, it looks like you stayed up all night.

158
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:37,131
Even in a title match, I think it's a long shot that would be impossible.

159
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:43,596
(Torataro) No, it's very quiet and hasn't fallen down, right?

160
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,806
No, no way

161
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:52,104
And... I think so.

162
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:01,614
(Torataro) Ah.

163
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:06,535
Aah!

164
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:07,578
Oops…

165
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,373
(Rie) What... what? what happened?

166
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:16,629
Um... this... my mom recommended this to me because she was concerned about my skin...

167
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:18,589
excuse me

168
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,343
-(Tatsumi) Ah-(Torataro) Ah.

169
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:25,971
(Tatsumi) Um... this.

170
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:27,264
(Torataro) Yeah?

171
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:29,892
(Tatsumi) Representative Tsuge on other media⸺

172
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:32,102
Interview with Mr. Komaki⸺

173
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:34,772
Check to see if they have made similar statements⸺

174
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:37,650
I have cleaned up everything related to the presidential election.

175
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,195
(Rie) What, did you do all this by yourself?

176
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:44,365
Thank you for your hard work.

177
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:46,116
(Torataro) Yes, this is it⸺

178
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:51,580
I think it will serve as supporting evidence to prove that the article is not fabricated.

179
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,085
What is “but”?

180
00:13:57,044 --> 00:14:02,841
Um...actually, I jammed into Ryumi-sensei's parents' house yesterday⸺

181
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:05,052
I heard about Usaha-san.

182
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:08,514
...And to be honest⸺

183
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:12,226
If it's too difficult for Dr. Ryumi to do this, I'm sure she'll let me out of this trial⸺

184
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:14,770
Do you think it doesn't matter at all?

185
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,690
Thank you for your consideration

186
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:22,027
But Mr. Komaki Toba appointed me as his agent.

187
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,864
So it would be rude if you didn't accept it.

188
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,574
(Rie) No, well, that's true...

189
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:30,536
I will do my best to win this case for my client.

190
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:34,206
That's what I can do now

191
00:14:39,086 --> 00:14:43,215
I understand, if Ryuumi-sensei says so.

192
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,511
Mr. Torataro, there is a place I want to go⸺

193
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:48,929
Could you please keep me company?

194
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:52,391
Yes, it's fine, but

195
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,023
(Employee) If it's the Kurosu desk, it's over there.

196
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:01,817
(Naomi) Impossible! When interviewing, first record

197
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:05,279
(Naozane) It's the evidence that speaks in the end, isn't it?

198
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:06,488
(Reporter) I understand.

199
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:17,625
Um... this is Kurosu's desk, this is lawyer Fuda.

200
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:19,460
This is Tendo

201
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:23,631
Maybe it's about the Komaki trial?

202
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:24,715
(Torataro) Yes

203
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,261
(Torataro) About the article written by Mr. Komaki⸺

204
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:30,804
I would like to ask you something.

205
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,265
Do you think Mr. Kurosu was a fabricator?

206
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:34,975
Still too straight

207
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:38,228
Komaki is a mid-career recruit and has a short career.

208
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:41,398
I'm the type of person who's serious and can't do anything crooked.

209
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,484
Same as shogi style

210
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:46,111
So what is the content of that article...

211
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:50,240
Since Komaki wrote it, I think he is conveying the truth.

212
00:15:51,116 --> 00:15:52,785
...If so, testify about what you just said in court.

213
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:53,952
(Sakate) I'm in trouble.

214
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:58,749
(Sakate) Regarding the trial, we have to go through the legal department.

215
00:15:58,832 --> 00:16:01,001
(Torataro) Um... how about this one?

216
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:03,754
This is Sakate, the news manager.

217
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:05,881
Even if you are a lawyer, you will be in trouble if you imitate someone without your permission.

218
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,342
The news manager is in charge of articles, right?

219
00:16:08,425 --> 00:16:10,678
Why did you delete the article so quickly?

220
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:13,514
The station has no choice but to take appropriate action since the protest has come...

221
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:16,934
(Torataro) Is it because the other party is a politician?

222
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:20,229
Was there any pressure other than protests?

223
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:21,772
On the other hand, I think he was arrogant...

224
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:24,400
I'm sorry, but I can't help Komaki-kun.

225
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,277
Please don't do what you want too

226
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:30,572
Hey, check this out.

227
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:37,454
We'll find out eventually, but Sakate will be the news manager⸺

228
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:41,000
It appears that Representative Tsuge has requested that he appear as a witness.

229
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,627
Are you a witness for the plaintiff?

230
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:47,005
I think the purpose is to provide testimony that questions the authenticity of the article.

231
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:52,094
Ah, it looks like the first mover has prepared some very strong pieces.

232
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:54,304
I have to go back and prepare countermeasures.

233
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:55,848
(Tatsumi) I'm back now.

234
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:56,890
Thank you for your hard work

235
00:16:58,642 --> 00:17:00,060
(Tatsumi) Ah.

236
00:17:00,144 --> 00:17:01,687
I heard it from Rie-san.

237
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:06,191
It seems like Ryumi is an aggressive person to jump into the game all of a sudden.

238
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:08,068
Did you harvest anything?

239
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:13,949
News Director Sakate was called as a witness for the plaintiff.

240
00:17:14,032 --> 00:17:19,163
Huh... As expected, there is only a former yameken.

241
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:22,374
Take measures now regarding this

242
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:26,336
Um... I thought about it if it was Joki.

243
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:40,184
In other words, the plaintiff in this case is a former prosecutor's lawyer.

244
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:42,853
There is no doubt that he is skilled in courtroom tactics.

245
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:47,399
In that case, we should use a quick attack from the opposing rook.

246
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:52,446
As expected from Ryumi-sensei, when it comes to shogi, things suddenly go into gear.

247
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:54,656
 Against a rook opponent⸺

248
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:57,993
It is a strategy to move rooks in the same direction.

249
00:17:58,077 --> 00:18:01,288
If the first player uses News Director Sakate as the offensive axis⸺

250
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:02,831
This is also a big piece⸺

251
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,000
I think I should call the Kurosu desk.

252
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:08,879
The Kurosu desk should be an unexpected witness for the first mover.

253
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:12,049
If the other side makes even the slightest mistake in their response, they can win all at once.

254
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:15,719
Even if you respond accurately, you can have a nearly even fight.

255
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:18,305
I see, it feels kind of convincing.

256
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:19,556
oh certainly

257
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:20,766
How about that?

258
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:21,683
(Torataro) Huh?

259
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,061
(Usaha) The rook facing her seems to be an aggressive Ryumi though⸺

260
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:26,688
I think it's best to avoid the Kurosu desk.

261
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:29,525
Why...?

262
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:33,070
Mr. Kurosu said that Mr. Usaba's article was correct⸺

263
00:18:33,153 --> 00:18:34,696
Perfect for a witness.

264
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:38,575
As someone in the department, it's natural that there will be pressure from above⸺

265
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:40,911
Even if I appear in court, it will not be as I wish⸺

266
00:18:40,994 --> 00:18:43,455
There is a risk that you may not be able to testify.

267
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:49,628
In that case, perhaps it would be better to avoid people involved in the news department?

268
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:50,838
(Torataro) Hmm.

269
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:52,923
(Usagiha) By the way, if it were me...

270
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:59,388
In this game, point with the right ball.

271
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:05,894
(Korataro) This is the first time I've seen Ryumi-sensei being denied Josei.

272
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:09,314
No, in the first place, I am going to talk about the policy of the trial in terms of the rules of shogi.

273
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:12,025
I think it's amazing that you don't feel any discomfort.

274
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:13,819
(Rabbitha) The right ball is⸺

275
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:17,698
If the first player comes with a rook, place this ball on the right⸺

276
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:20,951
This is a tactic that minimizes the effectiveness of your opponent's attacks.

277
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:25,706
The right ball has a balanced attack and defense strategy⸺

278
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:30,377
The ball's defense is weak, and in the worst case, there is a risk of it being attacked...

279
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:33,422
(Usagiba)...Even if that's the case, you still don't know the opponent's strategy⸺

280
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:35,340
I think the right ball is best here.

281
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:38,719
But you can't win this game without the opposing rook.

282
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:50,689
...In that case, could Kotaro-sensei decide?

283
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:55,193
Which tactic should I use in this trial?

284
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:56,320
Huh?

285
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,489
ah…

286
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:03,410
Ah, I understand

287
00:20:04,202 --> 00:20:06,663
A lawyer is the one who follows the client's wishes.

288
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,626
Let's go with Migigyoku

289
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,920
(Rabbitha) Thank you very much.

290
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:17,799
...If that's the case, I'll do a little more research on Representative Tsuge.

291
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:23,722
(Rie) Well, I'll deliver the documents to the district court.

292
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:24,640
The rest please

293
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:25,974
Understood

294
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:30,812
- (Torataro) Come on in. - (Rie) Yes, I'll come.

295
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:36,735
(Sound of door opening and closing)

296
00:20:36,818 --> 00:20:40,322
Mr. Kotaro, I have a request for you.

297
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:52,042
(Torataro) Representative Tsuge, he did not appear in court.

298
00:20:52,125 --> 00:20:55,212
I think I can win even if I don't show up.

299
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:21,613
(Kasumi) During the encouragement session, Ryumi attacked like fire.

300
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:26,034
On the other hand, Toba-chan had an impregnable uke style.

301
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:32,457
I see, so that's why we bumped into each other on this fixed track.

302
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:36,753
You said you bumped into each other... Toba-chan and Ryumi?

303
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,088
Mr. Ryumi is⸺

304
00:21:38,171 --> 00:21:40,757
I said we should go on the opposite rook⸺

305
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:43,385
Mr. Usaba claims the right ball.

306
00:21:43,468 --> 00:21:48,390
Right ball? But if that's the case, the goal is...

307
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:50,142
(Secretary) Please stand up.

308
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:58,525
(Presiding Judge) Now, the plaintiff, please begin questioning the witnesses.

309
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:02,696
The first mover does not rush to decide on a strategy from the beginning, so to speak...

310
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:04,781
Igyoku stance

311
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:09,369
On the other hand, the player on the draw goes to the right with 6 and 2 balls on the 34th move.

312
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:14,791
(Hirano) I would like to ask you to testify as the head of the news department.

313
00:22:15,792 --> 00:22:18,795
Every reporter has an article that only he or she can write.

314
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,338
Is it something you want to write about?

315
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:21,256
(Tatsumi) The first player was waiting to see.⸺

316
00:22:21,339 --> 00:22:24,092
If they start attacking, there are two options.

317
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:25,344
(Sakate) Of course.

318
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,179
That's my habit as a reporter.

319
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:30,098
If you are a reporter who wants to improve your reputation⸺

320
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,224
Is it even more so?

321
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:35,854
Yes, Komaki-kun had a strong desire to rise.

322
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:38,982
(Hirano) From the way the witness is saying it now⸺

323
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:40,400
That interview⸺

324
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:43,153
So that the defendant gets the scoop for himself⸺

325
00:22:43,236 --> 00:22:47,199
Do you mean that you interpreted it to your advantage and wrote the article?

326
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:51,119
(Tatsumi) First move: 2-4 steps The first offensive move made by the plaintiff.

327
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:53,246
- (Torataro) Objection, leading questioning... - (Sakate) Yes, I think so.

328
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:55,540
(Hirano) That’s it, yeah.

329
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:06,176
(Presiding Judge) Defendant, please begin cross-examination.

330
00:23:06,259 --> 00:23:07,469
yes

331
00:23:11,306 --> 00:23:14,101
Defendant's attorney Ayuda asks a question.

332
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:18,814
The witness graduated from the same university as Representative Tsuge, right?

333
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:23,443
Yes, that's right, but

334
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:26,863
(Torataro) Moreover, they belong to the same circle's alumni club.

335
00:23:26,947 --> 00:23:29,908
Did you know Representative Tsuge?

336
00:23:29,991 --> 00:23:32,828
I'm sure we've met several times.

337
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:35,288
If you are a senior at the university and know someone⸺

338
00:23:35,372 --> 00:23:39,126
Do you ever have any feelings of favoritism toward Representative Tsuge?

339
00:23:39,209 --> 00:23:42,087
They are just university seniors and juniors⸺

340
00:23:42,170 --> 00:23:44,548
There's nothing like what you're saying.

341
00:23:45,215 --> 00:23:49,010
So, would you be happy if Congressman Tsuge became prime minister?

342
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:51,555
This is a meaningful question that has nothing to do with this lawsuit.

343
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:54,641
The news department, who is in charge of the news department, reviews the content of the article.

344
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:57,477
This is an important question that asks how you perceived it.

345
00:23:59,354 --> 00:24:02,023
Of course I'm happy...I think

346
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:03,984
(Torataro) ...If that's the case, in an interview⸺

347
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:06,736
To find out from the plaintiffs about their desire to run for president⸺

348
00:24:06,820 --> 00:24:09,114
Were you expecting a witness?

349
00:24:09,197 --> 00:24:12,784
I'm sure there were expectations like that, but...

350
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:14,369
(Torataro) Such an important interview⸺

351
00:24:14,452 --> 00:24:16,663
For a defendant with a short career and a strong desire to move up⸺

352
00:24:16,746 --> 00:24:18,957
Isn't it a contradiction to leave it to you alone?

353
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:19,875
No, that's...

354
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:22,544
(Torataro) So, it's not just Komaki Toba-san.

355
00:24:22,627 --> 00:24:25,255
We cannot get the word out about the presidential election⸺

356
00:24:25,338 --> 00:24:26,590
Did you think about it beforehand?

357
00:24:26,673 --> 00:24:27,716
No, that's not true...

358
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,801
(Torataro) Did you think you could pull it out?

359
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:32,679
Well, it depends on the flow...

360
00:24:32,762 --> 00:24:36,224
Today's Kotaro-sensei is different from usual.

361
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:38,602
This question...

362
00:24:42,439 --> 00:24:46,151
If the second hand returns the ball that went up to the right with 5 and one ball⸺

363
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:48,111
There is only one aim

364
00:24:48,195 --> 00:24:49,696
(Torataro) I'll ask you again.

365
00:24:49,779 --> 00:24:52,407
In this interview, Representative Tsuge talks about his desire to run for president.

366
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:55,285
Was it done with the purpose of getting it out?

367
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:57,579
Of course I had expectations.

368
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:00,290
But why the news manager himself?

369
00:25:00,373 --> 00:25:03,960
Wasn't one of the reporters with more experience than the defendant in charge?

370
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:06,254
No, that's...

371
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:08,298
(Torataro) I'll ask you again.

372
00:25:08,381 --> 00:25:12,010
Does that mean you recognize her ability as a reporter?

373
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:16,765
I feel like I spend too much time asking the same questions.

374
00:25:18,934 --> 00:25:20,268
No way...

375
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:30,779
(Tatsumi) Same situation 3 times

376
00:25:31,529 --> 00:25:34,866
Kotaro sensei's aim is Sennichite!

377
00:25:35,450 --> 00:25:36,993
It will be a draw on the 4th time.

378
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:42,249
(Torataro) Now, I will ask the witness as the defendant's boss.

379
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:44,125
Please answer honestly

380
00:25:44,793 --> 00:25:46,836
(Tatsumi) Usa-chan's aim is...

381
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,130
I looked at the article before it was published and gave it the OK⸺

382
00:25:49,214 --> 00:25:53,134
Is it because you have determined that the legislator's statement has credibility?

383
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:55,053
Please answer “yes” or “no”

384
00:25:56,429 --> 00:25:58,348
(Rie) If “yes” to this question⸺

385
00:25:58,431 --> 00:26:00,809
I would like to confirm the authenticity of the article.

386
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:05,063
If “No”, then the responsibility cannot be placed solely on Mr. Usaba.

387
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:11,653
I can't answer right now

388
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:14,406
 (Tatsumi) Against 5 balls on the draw⸺

389
00:26:14,489 --> 00:26:15,907
First move 15 steps

390
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:18,451
Plaintiff avoids Sendai-te

391
00:26:21,454 --> 00:26:22,872
(Torataro) Chief Judge⸺

392
00:26:22,956 --> 00:26:26,167
Today's deadline is unlikely to be finished within the scheduled time⸺

393
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:29,296
I hope you will continue to interrogate me on the next date.

394
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:36,052
(Presiding Judge) I will allow questioning on the next date.

395
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:38,722
That's all

396
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:50,567
(Tatsumi) Usa-chan's aim is to buy time.

397
00:26:57,699 --> 00:27:00,410
Why buy time?

398
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:05,790
Ah, no, that’s from her “This trial⸺”

399
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:08,585
I was told, "I want you to postpone it as much as possible."

400
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:12,339
(Rabbitha) Mr. Kotaro, I have a request for you.

401
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:17,969
I want this trial to be postponed as long as possible.

402
00:27:19,512 --> 00:27:21,139
Prolong it?

403
00:27:21,681 --> 00:27:23,767
footsteps)

404
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:34,235
(Tatsumi) The one who stuck to the right ball was⸺

405
00:27:34,986 --> 00:27:37,697
It was meant to be brought into the Sennichi Hand.

406
00:27:40,367 --> 00:27:43,912
I just did my best strategy in this situation.

407
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:45,997
Aiming for a draw from the beginning...

408
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,251
Doesn't look like Toba-chan

409
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,133
...even if

410
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,806
This is all I have now

411
00:28:07,685 --> 00:28:11,231
(Jinno) Well, you did a great job, Mr. Ayuda.

412
00:28:13,024 --> 00:28:16,736
(Kamino) Please tell us about your future court strategy.

413
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:18,822
(Torataro) What is it? Suddenly

414
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:21,324
I'm a web writer⸺

415
00:28:21,408 --> 00:28:23,118
My name is Shugo Kamino.

416
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:26,079
This trial is attracting attention on the internet.

417
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:27,414
Please leave a comment

418
00:28:27,497 --> 00:28:30,166
Please stop this

419
00:28:32,127 --> 00:28:34,170
I can't help it (sound of pressing a switch)

420
00:28:34,754 --> 00:28:37,715
-(Kinno) Then again... -(Rie) Yes, I won't fool you.

421
00:28:38,216 --> 00:28:41,094
Don't feel relieved just because it's gone

422
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:45,557
-(Tatsumi) Huh? -(Kanno) You're very alert.

423
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:50,270
Um... please don't get me wrong.

424
00:28:53,731 --> 00:28:57,736
This trial is quite deep.

425
00:28:57,819 --> 00:29:00,655
I'm a journalist too.

426
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:04,242
I've been doing a lot of research on Representative Tsuge.

427
00:29:06,619 --> 00:29:10,290
If you have any interesting information, please share it.

428
00:29:11,291 --> 00:29:12,709
Hey? teacher

429
00:29:12,792 --> 00:29:14,419
(Rie) Sorry, I'm busy here.

430
00:29:14,502 --> 00:29:15,587
Yes, let's go

431
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:20,759
I'll be waiting~

432
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:24,471
 (Tsuge) For such a simple trial⸺

433
00:29:24,554 --> 00:29:26,639
What are you struggling with?

434
00:29:27,223 --> 00:29:28,099
(Nakazumi) Honestly apologize⸺

435
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:30,185
There was also a reporter named Komaki who did not respond⸺

436
00:29:30,268 --> 00:29:31,853
As soon as there is a lawsuit,

437
00:29:31,936 --> 00:29:34,147
When I raised the white flag, I stepped on it.

438
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:37,734
If she persisted this long, she must be that woman⸺

439
00:29:37,817 --> 00:29:40,487
I guess I should consider having a recording.

440
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:44,240
In that case, it would be a bit troublesome...

441
00:29:44,324 --> 00:29:47,660
Such a recording alone is not conclusive evidence.

442
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:54,083
However, it seems necessary to be careful just in case.

443
00:29:54,167 --> 00:29:58,713
(Nakazumi) Don't worry, we have already taken the next step.

444
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:22,820
(Naozane) No visitation allowed. This had never happened before⸺

445
00:30:22,904 --> 00:30:24,197
Did something happen?

446
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:27,492
(Doctor) The patient's condition has not changed.

447
00:30:28,326 --> 00:30:30,411
Hospital policy has changed

448
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:31,996
By any chance⸺

449
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:36,209
Hasn't he regained consciousness?

450
00:30:36,292 --> 00:30:39,420
I don't have any more information for those who are not family members...

451
00:30:40,588 --> 00:30:43,675
(Nurse) Excuse me, please pick it up.

452
00:30:46,177 --> 00:30:47,971
(Rie) What I know now is⸺

453
00:30:48,054 --> 00:30:52,308
Usagi-san is trying to prolong this trial no matter what.

454
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:55,520
Why is there a need to postpone the trial in the first place?

455
00:30:56,437 --> 00:31:00,316
(Rie) Ah, now that I think about it, Representative Tsuge's cabinet reshuffle is scheduled for next month.

456
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:03,862
There are rumors that he might take up his first ministerial post.

457
00:31:03,945 --> 00:31:06,364
Representative Tsuge wants the trial to be over by then.

458
00:31:06,447 --> 00:31:09,826
We don't like long-term battles, so we have favorable conditions⸺

459
00:31:09,909 --> 00:31:15,123
Is Toba-san trying to hold out until he proposes reconciliation?

460
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:18,668
If that's the reason, I wish you'd told me in advance.

461
00:31:18,751 --> 00:31:21,504
Well, that's true.

462
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:25,008
After all, Toba-chan has nothing to do with us⸺

463
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:28,595
I can't help but feel like I have pieces that I haven't shown yet.

464
00:31:29,470 --> 00:31:32,599
The pieces you own aren't witnesses, right?

465
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:38,354
I can think of only one thing

466
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:42,358
There was a reporter named Jinno earlier⸺

467
00:31:42,442 --> 00:31:46,029
You pretended to stop the recorder and continued recording.

468
00:31:46,112 --> 00:31:48,364
Ah, yes, I saw through it.

469
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:50,909
Don't feel relieved just because it's gone

470
00:31:50,992 --> 00:31:54,871
(Tatsumi) Mr. Kurosu said this to his subordinates on Tokyo TV.

471
00:31:54,954 --> 00:31:56,831
When interviewing, first record

472
00:31:56,914 --> 00:31:59,208
(Tatsumi) She is Usagi's senior reporter.

473
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:01,461
Usaha-chan will follow the teachings⸺

474
00:32:02,045 --> 00:32:05,632
If Jinno used the same hands as people...

475
00:32:05,715 --> 00:32:09,886
(Tsuge) Ah... I'm not good at recording, so could you please stop?

476
00:32:09,969 --> 00:32:11,012
Ah...

477
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:15,975
I wish I could hear a deeper story without the recording⸺

478
00:32:16,059 --> 00:32:17,727
I'm grateful too

479
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,401
Is there a recording of the interview?

480
00:32:25,485 --> 00:32:28,196
(Rie) But you said there was no recorded data.

481
00:32:28,279 --> 00:32:31,908
This is a copy of the interview notes from that day, which I have kept as evidence.

482
00:32:31,991 --> 00:32:33,576
look at this part

483
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,912
The memo is blurred and disappears

484
00:32:35,995 --> 00:32:36,829
(Rie) Ah, that's true.

485
00:32:36,913 --> 00:32:39,040
Huh? Maybe the pen stopped writing halfway through this?

486
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:42,168
(Tatsumi) The memo is restored on the next page⸺

487
00:32:42,251 --> 00:32:45,088
The thickness of the font is slightly different

488
00:32:45,171 --> 00:32:46,714
(Torataro) Didn't you change to a different pen?

489
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:53,012
(Tatsumi) Yes...and if you look at the article that corresponds to this memo part.

490
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:56,349
Just before the letters faded, Congressman Tsuge said⸺

491
00:32:56,432 --> 00:32:59,894
Talking about the evils of Japan's hereditary politics⸺

492
00:32:59,978 --> 00:33:01,813
There is also a note with the same description

493
00:33:01,896 --> 00:33:05,358
(Torataro) I did make a note saying “hereditary politics is wrong”.

494
00:33:05,441 --> 00:33:08,319
(Tatsumi) The article talks about the proportion of hereditary members⸺

495
00:33:08,403 --> 00:33:12,407
We cover details by ruling party, opposition party, etc.

496
00:33:12,490 --> 00:33:16,536
...but the memo doesn't have any of these numbers.

497
00:33:16,619 --> 00:33:19,330
(Rie) Congressman Tsuge was talking even while I was changing pens⸺

498
00:33:19,414 --> 00:33:21,416
Did you forget to take notes?

499
00:33:21,499 --> 00:33:25,878
How did you come up with the specific numbers in the article?

500
00:33:25,962 --> 00:33:29,048
Because you were recording it, you were able to listen to it again and write about it later?

501
00:33:29,757 --> 00:33:32,260
(Tatsumi) It's just one possibility.

502
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:35,722
Wait, wait, wait, wait, just in case there's a recording⸺

503
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:39,017
You could easily win this trial, so why are you hiding it?

504
00:33:40,018 --> 00:33:42,729
Even though the interviewee asked me not to record him.

505
00:33:42,812 --> 00:33:47,734
If I secretly recorded it, it would be an unethical act for me as a reporter.

506
00:33:47,817 --> 00:33:52,196
If I mess up, I might be disqualified as a journalist.

507
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:55,575
In other words, for Mr. Usaba, that recording was...

508
00:33:55,658 --> 00:33:57,869
At the same time as evidence to save yourself⸺

509
00:33:57,952 --> 00:34:01,414
This is a double-edged sword that could result in disqualification as a reporter.

510
00:34:01,497 --> 00:34:02,749
I couldn't show it publicly.

511
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:08,921
Even if that's the case, why doesn't Toba-chan tell us that?

512
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,219
After all, Toba-chan...

513
00:34:20,183 --> 00:34:21,476
Sorry

514
00:34:26,856 --> 00:34:27,899
(sound of door closing)

515
00:34:38,785 --> 00:34:41,037
(Sound of door opening and closing)

516
00:34:55,259 --> 00:34:58,930
You don't look so difficult during your snack break.

517
00:35:01,015 --> 00:35:06,187
In official games, snack breaks are also part of the allotted time.

518
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:13,986
I guess you're still dragging things with Toba-san after all.

519
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:15,363
Well, I can't help it.

520
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:17,114
No, I'm not dragging it out...

521
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:20,993
No, but to be honest, she's not the usual Ryumi-sensei.

522
00:35:21,077 --> 00:35:23,037
You know that yourself, right?

523
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:35,424
I just can't read Toba-chan's feelings.

524
00:35:37,593 --> 00:35:40,179
You can read shogi moves like that.

525
00:35:42,890 --> 00:35:48,062
Even if Toba-chan is hiding something⸺

526
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:50,898
If you don't tell me that

527
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:52,316
That's...

528
00:35:57,029 --> 00:35:58,656
Yeah? What is that?

529
00:36:02,785 --> 00:36:06,414
(Tatsumi) Toba-chan is the one who made me lose my friends⸺

530
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:09,041
I still haven't forgiven you for what I said.

531
00:36:10,543 --> 00:36:12,086
I feel like that

532
00:36:14,964 --> 00:36:16,591
(Rie) If that's the case, why is Toba-san?

533
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:18,718
Did you ask for Ryumi-sensei?

534
00:36:20,803 --> 00:36:22,179
it is…

535
00:36:26,184 --> 00:36:30,897
It's true that the current Toba-san is hiding something and isn't opening up to him.

536
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:34,358
But it's because of this situation⸺

537
00:36:34,442 --> 00:36:37,904
Maybe you came here because you wanted someone to help you?

538
00:36:47,204 --> 00:36:49,373
Believe the client no matter what

539
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:52,710
This is the motto of Ayuda Law Office.

540
00:36:55,546 --> 00:36:58,799
(Tatsumi) That's Torataro-sensei's father...

541
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:02,261
(Rie) Yes, Professor Youjiro was really excellent.

542
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:06,307
The client is hiding something or lying.

543
00:37:06,390 --> 00:37:09,602
I don't want to be hurt if the trial doesn't go well.

544
00:37:09,685 --> 00:37:10,978
There was as much as I wanted

545
00:37:12,647 --> 00:37:17,276
But even at times like that, Yojiro-sensei said,

546
00:37:18,277 --> 00:37:22,490
(Hijiro) Everyone who comes here is more or less injured⸺

547
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:24,408
asking for help

548
00:37:27,244 --> 00:37:32,625
Even if you lie, if it's a lie to hide the hurt⸺

549
00:37:32,708 --> 00:37:37,588
Until I dared to believe and was fooled and told the truth⸺

550
00:37:38,464 --> 00:37:41,592
Step by step, we close the distance and face each other

551
00:37:42,134 --> 00:37:45,763
That's our job.

552
00:37:45,846 --> 00:37:47,848
♪～

553
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:52,311
Did you understand now?

554
00:37:54,897 --> 00:37:57,066
The “po” of each step is⸺

555
00:37:57,149 --> 00:37:59,402
I applied to this “Ayumu” “Ayumu” from Ayuta Law Office.

556
00:37:59,485 --> 00:38:02,321
laughter)

557
00:38:02,405 --> 00:38:05,533
Huh? Didn't you get it across very well?

558
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:10,830
The kanji ``Ayumu''...

559
00:38:10,913 --> 00:38:15,543
(Rie) Sensei: You don't have to be oblivious after a good story.

560
00:38:15,626 --> 00:38:17,670
laughter)

561
00:38:17,753 --> 00:38:20,297
There's still something we can all do, right?

562
00:38:20,381 --> 00:38:21,424
(Lawyers) Yes.

563
00:38:25,344 --> 00:38:27,013
This is all I have now

564
00:38:27,722 --> 00:38:29,515
Maybe Toba-chan?

565
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:34,562
Maybe you have something that you can't tell anyone about.

566
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:42,403
Step by step, we close the distance and face each other

567
00:39:07,344 --> 00:39:09,347
～♪

568
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:10,848
(mail reception sound)

569
00:39:12,808 --> 00:39:13,642
(Torataro) Oh?

570
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:16,979
(sound of key press)

571
00:39:20,691 --> 00:39:22,568
S.J...

572
00:39:23,903 --> 00:39:25,237
Let's share

573
00:39:30,951 --> 00:39:34,580
(Torataro) Hello, you're Jinno-san, right?

574
00:39:34,663 --> 00:39:37,583
(Kinno) Yes, did you see my email?

575
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:40,336
Let me get straight to the point.

576
00:39:40,419 --> 00:39:43,881
Apparently there was actually audio recording of the interview with Representative Tsuge.

577
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:47,510
Was that secretly recorded by Komaki Toba?

578
00:39:47,593 --> 00:39:51,639
(Kanno) Yeah, and I'm planning to sell her recording data.

579
00:39:51,722 --> 00:39:53,432
Sell...

580
00:39:56,227 --> 00:39:59,188
Who are you selling it to?

581
00:39:59,271 --> 00:40:02,400
This is Representative Tsuge.

582
00:40:06,153 --> 00:40:09,990
(Tsuge) I'm not good at recording, so could you please stop?

583
00:40:10,074 --> 00:40:15,246
(Usaha) If you could tell a deeper story without recording...

584
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:18,624
(Kinno) If you can get the legislators to buy it without disclosing it in court⸺

585
00:40:18,707 --> 00:40:22,294
I don't have to be disqualified as a reporter, and I don't have to ruin the reputation of a lawmaker.

586
00:40:22,378 --> 00:40:24,380
A deal that kills two birds with one stone

587
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:25,756
...Right?

588
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,425
No way...

589
00:40:27,508 --> 00:40:29,468
(Kinno) He also tried to prolong the trial⸺

590
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:33,931
I think it was a tactic to raise the purchase price.

591
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:38,269
Representative Tsuge tonight from 7pm⸺

592
00:40:38,352 --> 00:40:41,438
I suddenly had plans to have a dinner at a restaurant called Ichi's House⸺

593
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:43,899
So you should negotiate with her.

594
00:40:45,151 --> 00:40:47,111
What Representative Tsuge always uses is⸺

595
00:40:48,028 --> 00:40:49,905
This is the pine room in the back.

596
00:40:50,656 --> 00:40:52,575
Haha...

597
00:40:57,246 --> 00:41:00,124
(Landlady) Dear customer, I am in trouble, please pick it up.

598
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:05,337
Haha... Huh?

599
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:10,009
-(Member) What is it? Are you - (Member) some media?

600
00:41:10,092 --> 00:41:12,469
(Member) What's going on with security! ?

601
00:41:12,553 --> 00:41:13,929
Oh no, I...

602
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,015
ah…

603
00:41:16,932 --> 00:41:21,896
Are you sure that you are the teacher representing reporter Komaki?

604
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:25,483
Yes, my name is Ayuda.

605
00:41:26,609 --> 00:41:29,737
(Tsuge) We would like to invite our seniors here⸺

606
00:41:29,820 --> 00:41:35,492
This is an extremely important meeting to hear opinions regarding policy.

607
00:41:35,576 --> 00:41:37,620
No one other than those involved is allowed to enter⸺

608
00:41:37,703 --> 00:41:39,830
It's a private area

609
00:41:39,914 --> 00:41:41,207
you understand

610
00:41:42,750 --> 00:41:45,169
very sorry! It seems there was some misunderstanding...

611
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:49,256
This is not just a misunderstanding, this is a grave situation.

612
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:50,299
Huh?

613
00:41:50,382 --> 00:41:53,886
You are in a building guarded by people⸺

614
00:41:53,969 --> 00:41:55,471
Committed an act of trespassing⸺

615
00:41:55,554 --> 00:41:58,849
Despite receiving a request to leave

616
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:01,018
Failure to leave the area

617
00:42:04,772 --> 00:42:08,108
Building trespassing and⸺

618
00:42:08,192 --> 00:42:10,903
There is a possibility that you will be charged with failure to leave.

619
00:42:13,822 --> 00:42:14,990
(Landlady) This is it.

620
00:42:15,074 --> 00:42:16,700
A suspicious person entered this room without permission...

621
00:42:18,118 --> 00:42:19,495
(Officer) Kita-Ushigome Police Station

622
00:42:19,578 --> 00:42:21,121
We have received a report.

623
00:42:21,205 --> 00:42:22,623
(Landlady) It's that person.

624
00:42:22,706 --> 00:42:23,624
 (Torataro) Yes?

625
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:24,750
(Officer) Anyway, at the police station...

626
00:42:24,833 --> 00:42:25,960
 (Torataro) Ah, ah, no...

627
00:42:26,043 --> 00:42:27,169
 (Torataro) Please let go!

628
00:42:27,253 --> 00:42:28,504
 (Officer) You have to be quiet⸺

629
00:42:28,587 --> 00:42:29,964
I will arrest you for obstructing official duties.

630
00:42:30,047 --> 00:42:31,131
 (Torataro) It's some kind of misunderstanding.

631
00:42:31,215 --> 00:42:32,800
I'm a lawyer...

632
00:42:32,883 --> 00:42:33,717
Mr. Jinno

633
00:42:34,593 --> 00:42:35,803
(Officer) Come on, hurry up and get on!

634
00:42:35,886 --> 00:42:38,430
 (Torataro) Hey...listen!

635
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:42,685
 (siren)

636
00:42:45,729 --> 00:42:51,735
Haha... I was able to take a nice video.

637
00:42:51,819 --> 00:42:53,821
 (phone ringtone)

638
00:42:53,904 --> 00:42:54,989
Yes, Ayuda's “Ayumu” is⸺

639
00:42:55,072 --> 00:42:58,200
At Ayuda Law Office, where we take each step step by step...

640
00:42:58,284 --> 00:43:01,620
Kita-Ushigome Police Station? yes

641
00:43:03,163 --> 00:43:04,248
Mr. Kotaro?

642
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:06,875
Did something happen to Kotaro-sensei?

643
00:43:07,626 --> 00:43:09,086
I was arrested.

644
00:43:10,379 --> 00:43:11,547
Arrested!?

645
00:43:12,631 --> 00:43:17,803
 (siren)

646
00:43:17,886 --> 00:43:20,389
I want to face Toba-chan

647
00:43:20,472 --> 00:43:22,016
(Usagiba) I've always wanted to hear it.

648
00:43:22,099 --> 00:43:23,058
Why did you do that?

649
00:43:23,142 --> 00:43:24,768
 (Torataro) This video is the purpose of me...

650
00:43:24,852 --> 00:43:25,769
I have a duty to report

651
00:43:25,853 --> 00:43:27,896
 (Usagiba) There is always a way out.

652
00:43:27,980 --> 00:43:28,814
(Tatsumi) Toba-chan now⸺

653
00:43:28,897 --> 00:43:29,815
You're not alone

654
00:43:29,898 --> 00:43:32,401
There is always a helping hand
